webpackJsonp([0xeac8172f11d2],{446:function(t,o){t.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:"<p>So after hosting my blog on Openshift, I started looking around so I can change the url’s from mydomain.rhcloud.com to mydomain.com, and it’s just as easy as editing the config.js file in the root of the ghost instance.</p>\n<p>I changed in the productions properties, the value for url</p>\n<p><code>url: 'http://'+process.env.OPENSHIFT_APP_DNS',</code></p>\n<p>top</p>\n<p><code>url: 'mydomain.com',</code></p>\n<p>after changing the valur for url I got something like this</p>\n<pre class='language-javascript'>\n<code class='language-javascript'>\nproduction: {  \n            //url: 'http://'+process.env.OPENSHIFT_APP_DNS,\n            url: 'http://www.mydomain.com',\n            mail: {},\n            .\n            .\n            .\n            more code.....   \n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>I’m cutting the rest of the file out for easy understanding.</p>\n<p>After making this modification and restarting my application, everything worked out great!!</p>",frontmatter:{path:"/openshift-ghost-url-config",title:"OPENSHIFT GHOST'S URL CONFIG",date:"April 21, 2016",tags:["ghost","cms","openshift"],author:{id:"Phanor Coll",bio:"Fullstack developer from Merida, Venezuela."}}}},pathContext:{}}}});
